[1] Case update
- Thu 30 Jan 2020. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/5151d8cef70a/situation-pidmiologique-du-30-janvier-2020?e=b8b1e1fcf3

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 29 Jan 2020:

Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases has been 3423, of which 3304 have been confirmed and 119 are probable. In total, there were 2244 deaths (2125 confirmed and 119 probable) and 1155 winners (healed persons or survivors);
- 542 suspected cases under investigation;
- 2 new confirmed cases in North Kivu, including 1 in Beni and 1 in Mabalako;
- 2 new deaths from confirmed cases, including 1 community death in North Kivu in Beni and 1 death from confirmed cases in North Kivu in Beni;
- 1 healed person leaving the Ebola treatment center in North Kivu in Beni;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 167 (approximately 5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

Vaccination
-----------
- A total of 8828 people were vaccinated with the 2nd vaccine Ad26.ZEBOV/MVA-BN-Filo (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health areas from Karisimbi to Goma;
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018 with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, 280 426 people have been vaccinated.

Surveillance at entry points
----------------------------
Since the start of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature measurement) at health checkpoints is 145 007 011.

