- Thu 30 Jan 2020. News scan
[CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy), abridged, edited]
http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2020/01/news-scan-jan-30-2020

The Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) tracked 2 more cases in an ongoing Ebola outbreak, raising the total to 3424, of which 2242 were fatal, according to the World Health Organization (WHO) online Ebola dashboard.

The latest daily update from the DRC's Ebola technical committee (CMRE) said one recent case noted on the WHO's dashboard yesterday was in Beni.

The CMRE also said 2 recent fatalities were in Beni, including one community death. Community deaths, which [take] place outside of a hospital or Ebola treatment center, raise the risk of community spread.

